<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910716-0051</DOCNO><DOCID>910716-0051.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Millipore Corp.:   Firm, Advanced Technology   Form Equipment Venture</HL><DATE>07/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MIL</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Millipore Corp. said it formed a joint venture withAdvanced Technology Materials Inc. to make peripheralequipment for gas systems used in making semiconductors.   The venture, Novapure Corp., will sell products thatremove impurities or toxic components from gases used by orgenerated from the manufacturing of semiconductors, thecompany added. The companies project the potential market tobe about $200 million.</LP><TEXT>   Under terms of the agreement, Advanced Technology willprovide &quot;the whole of its gas management systems division,including more than 15 issued and pending patents,&quot; Milliporesaid. Millipore added that it will provide equity funding anda research and development program at Novapure. Thecompanies' financial commitments to the venture weren'tdisclosed.   Millipore is a Bedford, Mass., analytical andpurifications products concern. Advanced Technology, based inDanbury, Conn., makes high-performance semiconductors andthin film processing technologies.</TEXT></DOC>